-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-26/metro-ag-s-kaufhof-to-expand-online-business-sueddeutsche-says.html
Metro AG (MEO)  wants to generate
3 percent of sales at its Kaufhof department-store division from
online business,  Sueddeutsche Zeitung  reported, citing Kaufhof
Chief Executive Officer Lovro Mandac.  Kaufhof is targeting annual sales of more than 100 million
euros ($146 million) in coming years by adding clothes to its
online store in the last few months of 2011, the newspaper cited
Mandac as saying in an interview.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Holger Elfes in Dusseldorf at 
 helfes@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Celeste Perri at   cperri@bloomberg.net . 